  "text": "## Deposits & Withdrawals  \n**Q: How do I deposit money?**\nA: You can deposit via:\n- **Bank Transfer:** FPS (immediate), BACS (next day)\n- **Branch Deposit:** Cash (at any FirstUK branch)\n- **Direct Transfer:** From salary/pension (set up with employer)  \n**Q: How do I withdraw money?**\nA: You can withdraw via:\n- **ATM:** Withdraw cash (£500/day limit)\n- **Bank Transfer:** Send to another bank account (1–2 days)\n- **Branch Teller:** Withdraw cash or check  \n**Q: Are there withdrawal limits?**\nA: No limits on transfers to other accounts. ATM withdrawals limited to £500/day.  \n**Q: Is there a charge to withdraw money?**\nA:\n- UK ATM withdrawal: £0\n- International ATM withdrawal: £2.50\n- Transfer to another account: £0  \n**Q: How quickly will my withdrawal go through?**\nA:\n- ATM cash withdrawal: Immediate\n- Transfer to another bank: 1–2 business days\n- Teller withdrawal: Immediate (if cash available)  \n---",
